replies.bodyText:
I confirmed this with @colings86 that multiple types were deprecated in 6.x and were not expected anymore.
if it contains two types it will get into else branch here https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/pull/54197/files#diff-9327cfc566910ab3fec1c4b23a87a71bR90
for v8 logic. It does not expect two types either, and in fact will consider this mapping not typed
MapperService.java
public static boolean isMappingSourceTyped(String type, Map<String, Object> mapping) {
        return mapping.size() == 1 && mapping.keySet().iterator().next().equals(type);
    }

the request with two types in a mapping will  eventually end up with
     "type": "mapper_parsing_exception",
        "reason": "Root mapping definition has unsupported parameters:  [some_type_2 : {properties={field1={type=text}}}] [some_type_1 : {properties={field1={type=text}}}]"
      }

Should we improve this or is this good enough?

